How you can make a difference 
The Vice President, Enterprise Applications (EA), reporting to the Chief Information Officer, will lead the go-forward strategy and operations for development, implementation, and management of enterprise application initiatives. They will manage a collaborative and transparent business and technology engagement model, where empowered technologists integrate into business teams, pursue a deep understanding of business functions along with the aligned technology needs, advocate opportunities for technology to become more effective, and proactively adapt technology services and process to support HealthEquityâ€™s strategic objectives along with each business departmentsâ€™ tactical outcomes. Additionally, the EA leader manages the budget and delivery of existing EA services, while continuously improving stability and quality, enabling our maniacal mindset towards teammate and customer satisfaction. 
What youâ€™ll be doing 
Provide technology vision and leadership for the development and implementation of Enterprise Application initiatives that create and maintain a strategic advantage
